<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98918382091490></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98918382091490><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/item.html?item=334&mid=98918382091490>Honestly Can't Tell</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, May 6th 5:17 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Lookin for opinions from those who have this and other high-end weaps.  I'm 56 Tank, and use Lammy in primary.  I have recently acquired CSS, another Lammy, and Bloodfire.  With my RBG and chanter haste, obviously I use the Lammy in primary, simply because of the speed, but I can't for the life of me tell the difference in taunt factor between the other weaps used in the offhand.  My dex is still under 100, so the Bloodfire doesnt proc that often in my offhand, unless we got a shammy in the group for a dex buff.  And the proc (blood boil) is not nearly the taunt I expected it to be.  The CSS hits the hardest in the offhand, but we're only talkin a few dmg points. And the Lammy is the quickest in the off.  Was just wonderin what some other  55+ tanks think.  Been askin friends in the game, and of course get a different opinion with each.<br><br>Thanks,<br>Mac<br>Tholuxe<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
